Git Command

=> to check the version of git
$git --version

=> to install git on ubunto
$sudo apt-get install git

=> to configure git
$ git config --global user.name		/ to set username  $git config --global user.name "user_name"

$git config --global user.email		/ to set useremail  $git config --global user.email "user_email"

=> to show the details of username and email 
$git config --list

=> list all files including hidden folder
$ls -al

=> to open a file
$gedit filename

=> to make a directory as git repository
$git init

=> to captured and build up file and directory locally
$git commit -m "comment" 

=> to pushed /upload the file or folder to a remote server
$git push -u origin master

to push force fully

$git push -u origin master -f

=> to add a directory to git repository
$git add file_name


